l%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Frbi-s-mpc-minutes-external-members-make-a-strong-case-for-a-rate-cut-124062100617_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Frbi-s-mpc-minutes-external-members-make-a-strong-case-for-a-rate-cut-124062100617_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Frbi-s-mpc-minutes-external-members-make-a-strong-case-for-a-rate-cut-124062100617_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hindujas%20Get%20Over%204%20Years%20In%20Jail%20For%20Exploiting%20Staff%20At%20Swiss%20Mansion%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20Swiss%20court%20handed%20jail%20sentences%20to%20four%20members%20of%20Britain's%20richest%20family%20on%20Friday%20for%20exploiting%20Indian%20staff%20at%20their%20Geneva%20mansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hindujas%20--%20who%20were%20not%20present%20in%20court%20--%20were%20acquitted%20of%20human%20trafficking%2C%20but%20convicted%20on%20other%20charges%20in%20a%20stunning%20verdict%20for%20the%20family%20whose%20fortune%20is%20estimated%20at%2037%20billion%20pounds%20(%2447%20billion).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrakash%20Hinduja%20and%20his%20wife%20Kamal%20Hinduja%20each%20got%20four%20years%20and%20six%20months%2C%20while%20their%20son%20Ajay%20and%20his%20wife%20Namrata%20received%20four-year%20terms%2C%20the%20presiding%20judge%20in%20Geneva%20ruled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cases%20stem%20from%20the%20family's%20practice%20of%20bringing%20servants%20from%20their%20native%20India%20and%20included%20accusations%20of%20confiscating%20their%20passports%20once%20they%20were%20flown%20to%20Switzerland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20argued%20the%20Hindujas%20paid%20their%20staff%20a%20pittance%20and%20gave%20them%20little%20freedom%20to%20leave%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20denied%20the%20allegations%2C%20claiming%20the%20prosecutors%20wanted%20to%20%26quot%3Bdo%20in%20the%20Hindujas%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hindujas%20reached%20a%20confidential%20out-of-court%20settlement%20with%20the%20three%20employees%20who%20made%20the%20accusations%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%2C%20the%20prosecution%20decided%20to%20pursue%20the%20case%20due%20to%20the%20gravity%20of%20the%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeneva%20prosecutor%20Yves%20Bertossa%20had%20requested%20a%20custodial%20sentence%20of%20five%20and%20a%20half%20years%20against%20Prakash%20and%20Kamal%20Hinduja.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAged%2078%20and%2075%20respectively%2C%20both%20had%20been%20absent%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20trial%20for%20health%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20closing%20address%2C%20the%20prosecutor%20accused%20the%20family%20of%20abusing%20the%20%26quot%3Basymmetrical%20situation%26quot%3B%20between%20a%20powerful%20employer%20and%20a%20vulnerable%20employee%20to%20save%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHousehold%20staff%20were%20paid%20salaries%20between%20220%20and%20400%20francs%20(%24250-450)%20a%20month%2C%20far%20below%20what%20they%20could%20expect%20to%20earn%20in%20Switzerland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20profiting%20from%20the%20misery%20of%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Bertossa%20told%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Not%20mistreated%20slaves'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Hinduja%20family's%20defence%20lawyers%20argued%20that%20the%20three%20plaintiffs%20received%20ample%20benefits%2C%20were%20not%20kept%20in%20isolation%20and%20were%20free%20to%20leave%20the%20villa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20not%20dealing%20with%20mistreated%20slaves%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicolas%20Jeandin%20told%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20employees%20%26quot%3Bwere%20grateful%20to%20the%20Hindujas%20for%20offering%20them%20a%20better%20life%26quot%3B%2C%20his%20fellow%20lawyer%20Robert%20Assael%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERepresenting%20Ajay%20Hinduja%2C%20lawyer%20Yael%20Hayat%20had%20slammed%20the%20%26quot%3Bexcessive%26quot%3B%20indictment%2C%20arguing%20the%20trial%20should%20be%20a%20question%20of%20%26quot%3Bjustice%2C%20not%20social%20justice%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENamrata%20Hinduja's%20lawyer%20Romain%20Jordan%20also%20pleaded%20for%20acquittal%2C%20claiming%20the%20prosecutors%20were%20aiming%20to%20make%20an%20example%20of%20the%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20argued%20the%20prosecution%20had%20failed%20to%20mention%20payments%20made%20to%20staff%20on%20top%20of%20their%20cash%20salaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20employee%20was%20cheated%20out%20of%20his%20or%20her%20salary%2C%26quot%3B%20Assael%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20staff%20even%20asked%20for%20raises%2C%20which%20they%20received.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20interests%20in%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20banking%20and%20healthcare%2C%20the%20Hinduja%20Group%20is%20present%20in%2038%20countries%20and%20employs%20around%20200%2C000%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718989380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fp4pu5mu8_hinduja-afp_625x300_18_June_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhindujas-get-over-4-years-in-jail-for-exploiting-staff-at-swiss-mansion-5941113%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Swiss%20court%20handed%20jail%20sentences%20to%20four%20members%20of%20Britain's%20richest%20family%20on%20Friday%20for%20exploiting%20Indian%20staff%20at%20their%20Geneva%20mansion.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhindujas-get-over-4-years-in-jail-for-exploiting-staff-at-swiss-mansion-5941113%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fw