statements%2Famp_articleshow%2F111174475.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Some%20People%20Are%20Protected%20Against%20Covid-19%2C%20Study%20Reveals%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20new%20study%20published%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Escience%20journal%20Nature%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20revealed%20why%20some%20people%20never%20get%20COVID-19%2C%20even%20after%20exposure.%20Researchers%20conducted%20a%20world-first%20experiment%20where%20they%20intentionally%20infected%20healthy%20volunteers%20with%20a%20pre-Alpha%20strain%20of%20SARS-CoV-2.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20found%20that%20people%20who%20resist%20infection%20have%20a%20much%20faster%20immune%20response%20in%20their%20nasal%20tissues%20compared%20to%20those%20who%20get%20sick.%20This%20response%20includes%20the%20activation%20of%20mucosal-associated%20invariant%20T%20(MAIT)%20cells%20and%20a%20drop%20in%20inflammatory%20white%20blood%20cells%2C%20which%20clear%20the%20virus%20before%20it%20sets%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41586-024-07575-x%5C%22%3EThe%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20found%20that%20people%20who%20resist%20infection%20have%20elevated%20expression%20of%20a%20gene%20called%20HLA-DQA2%20in%20nasal%20cells.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Christopher%20Chiu%2C%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Infectious%20Disease%20at%20Imperial%20College%20London%2C%20and%20who%20led%20the%20COVID-19%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imperial.ac.uk%2Fnews%2F254273%2Fimperials-human-challenge-study-helps-explain%2F%5C%22%3Ehuman%20challenge%20study%2C%20said%3A%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BThis%20paper%20highlights%20the%20value%20of%20the%20powerful%2C%20cutting-edge%20approaches%20applied%20through%20collaboration%20in%20the%20first-in-the-world%20SARS-CoV-2%20human%20challenge%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20programme%20of%20research%20continues%20to%20provide%20unique%20insights%20into%20how%20the%20immune%20system%20protects%20us%20from%20infection%20that%20cannot%20be%20achieved%20in%20any%20other%20setting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20only%20will%20these%20findings%20have%20an%20important%20impact%20on%20the%20development%20of%20next-generation%20interventions%20for%20SARS-CoV-2%2C%20but%20they%20should%20also%20be%20generalisable%20for%20other%20future%20outbreaks%20and%20pandemics.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20research%20could%20provide%20a%20basis%20for%20developing%20new%20treatments%20and%20vaccines%20that%20mimic%20these%20natural%20protective%20responses.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718988660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-04%2Fir3c0u5o_coronavirus-test-swab-pti-_625x300_14_April_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhy-some-people-are-protected-against-covid-19-study-reveals-5941090%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20groundbreaking%20study%20reveals%20that%20some%20people%20never%20contract%20COVID-19%20due%20to%20a%20rapid%20immune%20response%20in%20nasal%20tissues.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhy-some-people-are-protected-against-covid-19-study-reveals-5941090%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhy-some-people-are-protected-against-covid-19-study-reveals-5941090%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhy-some-people-are-protected-against-covid-19-study-reveals-5941090%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Olympus%20Capital%20Asia%20sells%209%25%20stake%20in%20Aster%20DM%20Healthcare%20for%20Rs%201%2C530%20cr%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718987732000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-12%2F01%2Fthumb%2Ffitandfill%2F400X400%2F1701451118-2503.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Folympu